    "description": "The practice of negotiation and persuasion in a myriad of social&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">situations. This skill covers knowledge of proper protocols, manners of&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">address and codes of conduct in diplomatic meetings, and haggling&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">over trading or contracts. This skill should also cover concepts of social&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">sciences, and can be used to make sense of customs from far off-world&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">cultures in a pinch.</span><div>• Haggle over a point on a business contract: opposed Diplomacy (INT) check&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">between the main negotiators involved.</span></div><div>• Get better prices with a bulk purchase: opposed Diplomacy (SOC) check&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">against the selling trader.</span></div><div>• Convince an unwilling character to become helpful: roll Diplomacy (SOC) 8+, or&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">more depending on how hard/costly it would be for both parties to be allied.</span></div>",
